Motor Racing



















Hamilton enjoys moment in the sun but remains reserved over F1 future

The Briton won a record-equalling fifth victory in his home Grand Prix on Sunday but refused to be drawn on his future



 






Hamilton dedicates British Grand Prix win to Silverstone home faithful









Hamilton wins British Grand Prix for record-equaling fifth time


  















Hamilton's Silverstone pole shows he delivers when the chips are down

After controversially deciding to give Wednesday’s London Live event a miss, Hamilton redeemed himself by taking pole position at Silverstone for Sunday's British Grand Prix



 






Hamilton qualifies on pole ahead of Raikkonen and Vettel









Hamilton satisfied by practice as Bottas handed five-place penalty 

















Hamilton unrepentant for missing F1 event before Silverstone

The Brit decided to go on holiday to Greece rather than join the other 19 drivers at a London demonstration


















Hamilton: 'Do people know how much I love the UK? Maybe not enough'

At times, the Mercedes driver seems like a prophet yet to be honoured by his people



  















Formula 1 take thinly-veiled swipe at Hamilton 

He decided to go on holiday instead of attending the event in London


















British GP at Silverstone in doubt as owners activate break clause

The owners of the circuit have sustained £7.6m losses across the last two years of staging the race



  















Hamilton keeps head down and works hard as F1 merry-go-round heats up

The Brit suffered yet more disappointment in missing out on another podium place


















McLaren in pole position as share sale paves way for seat on F1 board

Exclusive: McLaren is now on track to join the exclusive club of Ferrari and reigning champions Mercedes which both have a say in how F1 is run



 






Bottas comes of age to hold off Vettel and take win in Austria









Hamilton ready to 'give it everything' as teammate Bottas takes pole

















Hamilton and Vettel remain centre stage as Bottas takes Austrian pole

As is protocol the top three drivers were interviewed on the grid after the qualifying session, with the host asking for Vettel and Hamilton to shake hands only for the latter to walk away



  















Vettel has Ferrari focusing on the track again after tough few weeks

After weeks of controversy and a missing chief engine designer, the Italian constructor needed some relief


















Verstappen wants to leave Red Bull and join Ferrari next season

The Dutchman has reportedly asked to leave his current team ahead of the 2019 season


















Hamilton and Vettel put Baku incident behind them in Austria

Hamilton revealed the German apologised to him - but not immediately 



 






Hamilton: Vettel is showing weakness - I will beat him the right way









What happened between Hamilton and Vettel in Baku

















Hamilton refusing to talk to Vettel after Azerbaijan GP incident

Vettel received a 10 second stop and go penalty and three points on his racing licence for the move, which was generally condemned in the F1 paddock


















Vettel hits Hamilton as Ricciardo wins dramatic race in Azerbaijan

Valtteri Bottas finished second with Lance Stroll completing the podium



 






Hamilton saves the best until last as he claims pole in Baku









Verstappen sets the pace in second practice ahead of Azerbaijan GP

















Formula 1 owners reschedule US GP to accommodate Timberlake concert

Pop star Timberlake is due to perform at the Circuit of the Americas on the evening of Saturday October 21



  















Personal rivalries set to dominate proceedings for the Azerbaijan GP

Force India boss Bob Fernley said that the situation between Sergio Perez and Esteban Ocon could become a 'handful' for the team - but they aren't the only two at odds with one another



 






Alonso won't 'gamble' on 2018 seat as he considers his options









Hamilton open to retirement at end of the season

















Hamilton compares Mercedes domination to a punch from Mayweather

Mercedes landed a knockout blow to Ferrari's hopes of success in Montreal, with Hamilton and Valtteri Bottas taking first and second as Sebastian Vettel missed out on the podium


















Flawless Hamilton triumphs in Canada to put pressure on Vettel

The Mercedes driver is now only 12 points behind his German rival










Hamilton left emotional after equalling Senna's career pole record







London attack victims to be honoured with silence at Canadian GP







Raikkonen with a point to prove as 'bits and pieces' help Hamilton







Alonso could walk away from F1 if more races are added to the calendar







Kubica left with 'mixed feelings' after first F1 test in six years



















Hamilton aware he cannot afford Monaco Grand Prix repeat

Hamilton finished in seventh in what he called 'not a happy car'


















Heartbreak for Alonso as his Indy 500 ends with late engine failure

Alonso was in the top 10 with 21 laps remaining when he was forced to withdraw


















Five things we learned from the Monaco Grand Prix

Five things we learned: Wider cars make overtaking impossible, McLaren suffer a bitter blow and why Jenson Button's retirement just about summed up his weekend






 

 
 
 
 


