Sympathy Flowers







Patrick was born on December 27, 1951 and passed away on Sunday, May 29, 2016.
Patrick was a resident of Pooler, Georgia at the time of passing.
He retired after honorably serving his country in the U.S. Navy for 32 years. He proudly commanded USS Hercules PHM 2 USS Thomas S Gates CG 51 and USS Port Royal CG 73.
Patrick was married to Karen.
The memorial service to honor Patrick�s life will be on Sunday June 5 2016 at 4 p.m. at the Savannah Quarters Country Club located at 8 Palladian Way in Pooler. Full military honors will follow.
In lieu of flowers the family requests donations sent in Patrick's honor to the Navy Marine Corps Relief Society and youth golf program The First Tee of Savannah.










