May the God of all comfort strengthen you until you see him again in "Paradise". John 23:43




			
				
				Posted by: K B     Dec 12, 2016
			










Memories of serving with with Pat in BUNKER HILL will always be fondly remembered.  He was an inspirational leader and a man of genuine character. Our thoughts, prayers, and condolences to his family.  May he rest in peace and may his loved ones find comfort. Such a great loss.




			
				
				Posted by: Steve Kelley - Virginia Beach,  VA   Jun 22, 2016
			










Karen, I am so saddened to hear of your loss. Captain Allen was such an inspirational mentor and the greatest leader I have served with. I remember the many lessons he taught me, as I made so many mistakes as his "fill-in Chief Engineer" on Port Royal. In his typical fashion, he patiently led me to the answers and mentored me to success despite my best efforts. His lessons have stuck with me throughout my time as a leader.

... more





Karen, I am so saddened to hear of your loss.  Captain Allen was such an inspirational mentor and the greatest leader I have served with.  I remember the many lessons he taught me, as I made so many mistakes as his "fill-in Chief Engineer" on Port Royal.  In his typical fashion, he patiently led me to the answers and mentored me to success despite my best efforts.  His lessons have stuck with me throughout my time as a leader.  I remember convincing him to make a port call in Cabo San Lucas, nudging him with an opportunity to go on a fishing trip with my father's client who lived there.  What a great day that was, and he smiled the whole time, even reeled in a Marlin if I remember correctly.  Fond memories, and surely you have many.  My family prays for yours and he will be sorely missed by many.Fair winds and following seas shipmate.De Oppresso Liber,




			
				
				Posted by: Ryan Agee - Kaneohe,  HI   Jun 18, 2016
			










Dear Karen,Steve & I were deeply saddened by the news of Pat's untimely death. He was such a great man, husband, father and Naval officer, always giving his all. We will never forget the fun times we had with you and Pat in Yokosuka, and of course baby sitting Tracey and Richard. Heaven welcomed a special angel on May 29th.May God's love comfort you and help you find peace and healing in the days to come.~Steve & Amy Larsen




			
				
				Posted by: Steve and Amy Larsen - La Quinta,  CA   Jun 11, 2016
			










Karen,There are no words to tell you how sorry I am at Pat's passing. When I heard it from Richard F. my heart broke. You and your family are in my thoughts.




			
				
				Posted by: Jessica Lerner - ponte vedra beach,  FL   Jun 08, 2016
			










Karen - Pam and I were shocked and deeply saddened to hear or Pat's death. A truly remarkable man who made the hard things look easy and always achieved more than you expected he could. He was a key reason morale was so high on Bunker Hill and the ship was so successful. It was so great to see him get 3 ship commands during his career - how happy his crews must have been.We remember fondly our times together

... more





Karen - Pam and I were shocked and deeply saddened to hear or Pat's death.  A truly remarkable man who made the hard things look easy and always achieved more than you expected he could.  He was a key reason morale was so high on Bunker Hill and the ship was so successful.  It was so great to see him get 3 ship commands during his career - how happy his crews must have been.We remember fondly our times together in Japan - from the dog running loose in the airport to the fun times in Yokosuka.  Pat was always an instigator of having fun while doing an outstanding job.  You are in our prayers for comfort at this very difficult time.  We will be further in touch.....  May God bless you and all your family.




			
				
				Posted by: Rod and Pam Rempt - Big Sky,  MT   Jun 06, 2016
			










Please accept our sincere condolences..Pat was one of the first people I played golf with when I moved to Savannah. Always great company, and a real gentleman. Tonight I'll drink a pint in his honour.




			
				
				Posted by: Steve Dalton - Warwick England   Jun 05, 2016
			










Karen,Luanne and I were deeply saddened to hear of Pat's passing.  He was such a great man in so many ways and he had a profound positive impact on so many people. He was a humble man, and yet at the same time, a powerful leader who inspired confidence and that shone throughout his career.We will all miss him very much.  Our thoughts and prayers are with you and your family throughout this most difficult time.  John and Luanne Ailes




			
				
				Posted by: A friend   Jun 04, 2016
			










I hope there is a golf course in heaven because I know you will be on it.  We have been proud of you for your entire career.  Little brother, you will be in our hearts forever.  God bless you with fair winds and following seas.




			
				
				Posted by: Bill and Joyce Allen - Hagerstown,  MD   Jun 03, 2016
			










Having served with Pat in the Navy, I have always considered him a role model, mentor and friend.  He was truly a special leader and every place that he served was better when he left.  you always felt more positive after a conversation, watch at sea or liberty on the beach with Pat--he truly made a difference.  Jo Brooke and my thoughts and prayers are with all of you. Love, The Nowells




			
				
				Posted by: John Nowell - Okinawa Japan   Jun 03, 2016
			







